## Figure Evidence

Use figure evidence to connect imaging claims to representative diagnostic
images. Store images locally only when reuse is explicitly allowed. If reuse is
not allowed, uncertain, or limited to source-site viewing, link to the external
figure instead of downloading or committing the image.

For every figure, record metadata using:

```text
skillforge/templates/clinical-statistical-expert/disease-figure-evidence.md.tmpl
skillforge/templates/clinical-statistical-expert/disease.figures.schema.json
```

Use the helper when creating figure metadata:

```text
python -m skillforge figure-evidence <disease> --figure-id <id> --source-title "<title>" --source-url <url> --figure-label "Figure 31" --license "<license>" --reuse-status ok-to-embed --image-path <file> --clinical-point "<clinical point>" --section "<Disease.md section>" --json
```

When the figure is link-only or needs review, omit `--image-path` and use
`--reuse-status link-only` or `--reuse-status needs-review`.

